data.meta_desc: What should I absolutely not do when visiting the USA? Charlie Knoles, I have livedin5S countries + and am an Aussie expat in the USA. Don't get out of your car if you get pulled over by police. I was pulled over by a police officer while driving in Iowa. It was one week after I had arrived in the USA for the first time. I had accidentally made a minor mistake disobeying a traffic sign. Back home in Australia its considered polite to get out of your car and walk over to the police officers car and hand him your license so he doesn't have to get out of his seat. I wanted to be extra polite so I immediately jumped out of my car and walked towards his car while reaching into my back pocket. I'm lucky to be alive. If you come from a gun-free country like the UK or Australia you don't have any natural instinct for gun culture. You don't realize that police assume that. Gun Control.  Memes.
